        "teacherMoves": "Teacher points to the photograph and says: 'Before we say anything mathematical today, I want you to just look at this image. This was taken near Kisumu, on the shore of Lake Victoria, early in the morning when the water is perfectly still. Tell me — what do you notice? What do you wonder?' Allow 20 seconds of silent looking (WAIT TIME 1). Then: 'Now, on your sticky note, write your best scientific or mathematical prediction: why is the reflection exactly the same size as the boat?' After individual writing, ask one reporter per group to share. Teacher listens without evaluating, recording key prediction phrases on the board under the heading PREDICTIONS — DO NOT ERASE. Teacher then says: 'These are your ideas right now. By the end of this unit you will be able to prove whether each prediction is correct using formal mathematics.'",
